</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,854,1349]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,426,854,880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Body elongate ovate, covered with broad adpressed scales (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1175,855,881]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1922,1946]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[154,1433,181,1898]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species, dorsal view. 1, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, holotype, male; 2, E. (Azerberyxia) serratotibialis, paratype, female; 3, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) from Iran; 4, Eryxia (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 from Congo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503487/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Eyes large, elongate; genae short (
<figureCitation box="[299,369,891,918]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,197,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1434,181,1850]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species. 5, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, lateral view of holotype; 6, E. serratotibialis, head of holotype; 7, E. serratotibialis, dorsolateral view of right metatibia of holotype; 8, E. (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 right metatibia; 9, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) right metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503489/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Antennae filiform. Prothorax distinctly narrower than elytra, notosternal suture not evident. Elytra confusedly punctate. All tibiae dorsally finely serrate due to small spines arranged in unequal rows. Metatibiae with deep longitudinal excavation between raised outer and inner borders at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1198,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,197,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1434,181,1850]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species. 5, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, lateral view of holotype; 6, E. serratotibialis, head of holotype; 7, E. serratotibialis, dorsolateral view of right metatibia of holotype; 8, E. (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 right metatibia; 9, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) right metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503489/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,854,1349]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,999,1025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName box="[457,592,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Azerberyxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[457,592,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Azerberyxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed from part of country name 
<collectingCountry box="[1042,1165,999,1025]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
and generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Eryxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Eryxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,489,1070,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,854,1349]" box="[199,489,1070,1097]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1070,1096]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[358,485,1071,1097]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,854,1349]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1106,1132]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new subgenus differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1865" box="[816,891,1107,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Eryxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[816,891,1107,1132]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Eryxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[897,954,1107,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having serrate tibiae, large elongate eyes and flattened wider scales, covering the body. In the region of its distribution, 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1181,1143,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Azerberyxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1181,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Azerberyxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a comparatively large cylindrical pubescent body, is most similar to representatives of the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[1088,1244,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Falsonerissus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M." box="[1251,1359,1178,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" pagination="13 - 16" refId="ref3092" refString="Pic, M. (1951) Coleopteres du globe (suite). L'Echange, Revue Linneenne, 67 (526), 13 - 16." type="journal article" year="1951">Pic, 1951</bibRefCitation>
, of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Laporte, 1833" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" box="[224,543,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Colasposoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[224,376,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Colasposoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="de Laporte, M. F. L." box="[385,543,1215,1241]" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" pagination="18 - 25" refId="ref2862" refString="de Laporte, M. F. L. (1833) Memoire sur les divisions du genre Colaspis. Revue Entomologique, 1, 18 - 25." type="journal article" year="1833">Laporte, 1833</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[559,628,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1922,1946]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[154,1433,181,1898]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species, dorsal view. 1, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, holotype, male; 2, E. (Azerberyxia) serratotibialis, paratype, female; 3, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) from Iran; 4, Eryxia (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 from Congo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503487/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). But 
<taxonomicName box="[698,833,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Azerberyxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,833,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Azerberyxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized, like other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1865" box="[1267,1342,1215,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Eryxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1267,1342,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Eryxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1922,1946]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[154,1433,181,1898]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species, dorsal view. 1, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, holotype, male; 2, E. (Azerberyxia) serratotibialis, paratype, female; 3, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) from Iran; 4, Eryxia (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 from Congo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503487/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
), by having a narrow pronotum, obsolete notosternal sutures, squamose setae covering the body and hind tibiae with deep longitudinal excavation at apex (
<figureCitation box="[633,733,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,197,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1434,181,1850]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species. 5, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, lateral view of holotype; 6, E. serratotibialis, head of holotype; 7, E. serratotibialis, dorsolateral view of right metatibia of holotype; 8, E. (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 right metatibia; 9, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) right metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503489/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
); in contrast to the wide pronotum, well developed notosternal suture, fine dorsal pubescence and obliquely truncated apices of metatibiae (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1074,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,197,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1434,181,1850]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Eryxia species and Colasposoma species. 5, Eryxia (subgenus Azerberyxia) serratotibialis new species, lateral view of holotype; 6, E. serratotibialis, head of holotype; 7, E. serratotibialis, dorsolateral view of right metatibia of holotype; 8, E. (subgenus Eryxia) confusa Selman, 1972 right metatibia; 9, Colasposoma (subgenus Falsonerissus) argentatum (Lopatin, 1981) right metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4503489/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) in 
<emphasis box="[1118,1281,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Falsonerissus.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
